subparagraph.text:
the number of eligible public charter
				schools under the jurisdiction or in the service area of the eligible entity
				that are operating;

subclause.text:
the number of
				students enrolled in dual enrollment, Advanced Placement, International
				Baccalaureate, or other college level courses;

the number of
				students earning a professional certificate or license through the
				school;

clause.text:
identifying eligible public charter
				schools, or networks of eligible public charter schools, to receive subgrants
				under this section;

increasing the number of openings in
				eligible public charter schools for students attending identified schools and
				schools with a low graduation rate;

subclause.text:
closing public
				charter schools that do not meet acceptable standards of performance;
				and

clause.text:
eligible public charter schools that are
				operating in the State in which the eligible entity intends to award subgrants
				under this section;

subparagraph.text:
serves or plans to serve a large percentage
				of low-income students from identified schools or public schools with a low
				graduation rate;

provides evidence of effective monitoring
				of the academic success of students who attend public charter schools under the
				jurisdiction of the eligible entity;

has established
				goals, objectives, and outcomes for the proposed project that are clearly
				specified, measurable, and attainable;

clause.text:
provides strong evidence of support for
				public charter schools and has in place innovative policies that support
				academically successful charter school growth;

authorizes public charter schools to offer
				early childhood education programs, including prekindergarten, in accordance
				with State law;

subclause.text:
in the case of an eligible public charter
				school receiving a subgrant under this section, amends its charter to reflect
				the growth activities described in subsection (e);

the authorized public chartering agency’s
				strategic plan for authorizing or approving public charter schools and any
				progress toward achieving the objectives of the strategic plan;

the authorized public chartering agency’s
				transparent, timely, and effective process for closing down academically
				unsuccessful public charter schools;

clause.text:
support the physical expansion of school
				buildings, including financing the development of new buildings and campuses to
				meet increased enrollment needs;

subparagraph.text:
conducting credit enhancement initiatives
				(as referred to in subpart 2) in support of the development of facilities for
				eligible public charter schools serving students;

providing information to such parents and
				school officials at such schools regarding eligible public charter schools
				receiving subgrants under subsection (e);

increased student
				academic achievement and attainment for all students, including, as applicable,
				educationally disadvantaged students served by the charter school;

